The paper discusses a ranking framework for scientific literature search, which involves modeling inter-entity relationships and capturing entity type information. This aligns with several sub-categories in computer science, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Deep Learning (cs.DL), Databases (cs.DB), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). However, since the focus is on search algorithms and ranking models, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.CL and cs.DL, which deal with natural language processing and text analysis. cs.DB and cs.LG are also relevant due to their emphasis on data management and machine learning techniques, respectively.
